1
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:09,417
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:09,458 --> 00:00:11,250
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:14,041
FIRE...

4
00:00:14,083 --> 00:00:15,917
AIR.

5
00:00:15,959 --> 00:00:20,166
LONG AGO, THE 4 NATIONS
LIVED TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

6
00:00:20,208 --> 00:00:24,750
THEN, EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

7
00:00:24,792 --> 00:00:27,417
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL 4 ELEMENTS,

8
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:28,959
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,750
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST,

10
00:00:30,792 --> 00:00:32,375
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:32,417 --> 00:00:35,959
100 YEARS PASSED, AND MY BROTHER
AND I DISCOVERED THE NEW
AVATAR--

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,959
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

13
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS ARE GREAT,

14
00:00:40,041 --> 00:00:42,834
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

15
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:44,125
Aang: OOF!

16
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:46,542
Katara: BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

17
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:56,917
I'M THE AVATAR.

18
00:00:56,959 --> 00:00:58,458
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

19
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,083
THE LAST AVATAR
WAS AN AIRBENDER

20
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:01,834
WHO DISAPPEARED
100 YEARS AGO.

21
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:03,291
THAT'S ME.

22
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:04,792
I HAVE FRIENDS
ALL OVER THE WORLD,

23
00:01:04,834 --> 00:01:06,375
EVEN IN THE FIRE NATION.

24
00:01:06,417 --> 00:01:07,875
I'VE NEVER SEEN ANY WAR.

25
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:17,166
- SEND WORD
TO THE FIRE LORD
IMMEDIATELY.

26
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:20,041
THE AVATAR HAS RETURNED.

27
00:01:20,083 --> 00:01:24,166
- MONK GYATSO AND THE OTHER
AIRBENDERS MAY BE GONE,

28
00:01:24,208 --> 00:01:27,041
BUT YOU STILL HAVE A FAMILY.

29
00:01:27,083 --> 00:01:29,917
SOKKA AND I, WE'RE
YOUR FAMILY NOW!

30
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:31,291
I REALLY AM
THE LAST AIRBENDER.

31
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:46,000
THE EARTH KINGDOM
CITY OF OMASHU!

32
00:01:49,291 --> 00:01:51,417
I USED TO ALWAYS
COME HERE TO VISIT MY
FRIEND BUMI.

33
00:01:51,458 --> 00:01:55,083
WOW! WE DON'T HAVE CITIES LIKE
THIS IN THE SOUTH POLE.

34
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:57,291
THEY HAVE BUILDINGS
HERE THAT DON'T MELT.

35
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:58,959
WELL, LET'S GO,
SLOWPOKES.

36
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,792
THE REAL FUN
IS INSIDE THE CITY!

37
00:02:01,834 --> 00:02:03,333
WAIT, AANG.

38
00:02:03,375 --> 00:02:06,166
IT COULD BE DANGEROUS IF PEOPLE
FIND OUT YOU'RE THE AVATAR.

39
00:02:06,208 --> 00:02:07,875
YOU NEED A DISGUISE.

40
00:02:07,917 --> 00:02:09,291
SO, WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO,

41
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,792
GROW A MUSTACHE?

42
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:15,917
OH, THIS IS SO ITCHY.

43
00:02:15,959 --> 00:02:18,417
HOW DO YOU LIVE
IN THIS STUFF?

44
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:19,709
[SNORTS]

45
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:21,250
GREAT!

46
00:02:21,291 --> 00:02:22,959
NOW YOU LOOK JUST
LIKE MY GRANDFATHER.

47
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,458
TECHNICALLY,
AANG IS 112 YEARS OLD.

48
00:02:26,417 --> 00:02:29,083
NOW, LET'S GET TO SKIPPING,
YOUNG WHIPPERSNAPPERS!

49
00:02:29,125 --> 00:02:30,375
THE BIG CITY AWAITS!

50
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,917
Aang: YOU GUYS ARE
GONNA LOVE OMASHU.

51
00:02:48,959 --> 00:02:50,917
THE PEOPLE HERE ARE
THE FRIENDLIEST IN THE WORLD.

52
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:55,250
Man: WHAT KIND OF SLUM
DO YOU THINK THIS IS?!

53
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:03,250
NO! MY CABBAGES!

54
00:03:06,792 --> 00:03:08,166
JUST KEEP SMILING.

55
00:03:10,083 --> 00:03:11,208
HEH HEH HEH.

56
00:03:14,792 --> 00:03:15,834
STATE YOUR BUSINESS!

57
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:19,875
MY BUSINESS IS
MY BUSINESS, YOUNG MAN,

58
00:03:19,917 --> 00:03:21,083
AND NONE OF YOURS.

59
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:23,041
I'VE GOT HALF A MIND TO
BEND YOU OVER MY KNEE

60
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,834
AND PADDLE YOUR BACKSIDE.

61
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,625
SETTLE DOWN,
OLD TIMER.

62
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:28,542
JUST TELL ME
WHO YOU ARE.

63
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:33,208
NAME'S BONZOO
PIPPENPADLOPSICOPOLIS
THE THIRD.

64
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:35,166
AND THESE ARE MY GRANDKIDS.

65
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,375
HI. JUNE
PIPPENPADLOPSICOPOLIS.

66
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:39,959
NICE TO MEET YOU.

67
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,709
YOU SEEM LIKE
A RESPONSIBLE
YOUNG LADY.

68
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:45,250
SEE THAT YOUR GRANDFATHER
STAYS OUT OF TROUBLE.

69
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:46,083
ENJOY OMASHU.

70
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:47,083
WE WILL.

71
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:51,583
WAIT A MINUTE!

72
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:57,250
YOU'RE A STRONG YOUNG BOY.

73
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,959
SHOW SOME RESPECT
FOR THE ELDERLY

74
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,542
AND CARRY YOUR
GRANDFATHER'S BAG.

75
00:04:00,583 --> 00:04:02,125
GOOD IDEA.

76
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:33,166
Aang: THIS IS THE OMASHU
DELIVERY SYSTEM--

77
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:35,750
MILES AND MILES OF
TUBES AND CHUTES.

78
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,125
EARTHBENDING BRINGS
THE PACKAGES UP,

79
00:04:40,166 --> 00:04:43,250
AND GRAVITY
BRINGS THEM DOWN.

80
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:45,291
GREAT, SO THEY GET
THEIR MAIL ON TIME.

81
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:47,041
THEY DO GET THEIR
MAIL ON TIME.

82
00:04:47,083 --> 00:04:48,583
BUT MY FRIEND BUMI

83
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:50,208
FOUND A BETTER USE
FOR THESE CHUTES.

84
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:55,500
LOOK AROUND YOU!

85
00:04:55,542 --> 00:04:56,500
WHAT DO YOU SEE?!

86
00:04:56,542 --> 00:04:57,834
UM...

87
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:59,542
THE MAIL SYSTEM.

88
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:01,208
INSTEAD OF SEEING WHAT
THEY WANT YOU TO SEE,

89
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,792
YOU GOTTA OPEN
YOUR BRAIN

90
00:05:02,834 --> 00:05:04,667
TO THE POSSIBILITIES.

91
00:05:04,709 --> 00:05:06,709
A PACKAGE-SENDING SYSTEM?

92
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:10,208
THE WORLD'S GREATEST
SUPER SLIDE!

93
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:12,750
BUMI, YOU'RE
A MAD GENIUS.

94
00:05:12,792 --> 00:05:14,417
[LAUGHS]

95
00:05:14,458 --> 00:05:16,125
[SNORTS]

96
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:19,875
[BOTH LAUGHING]

97
00:05:19,917 --> 00:05:21,166
YEAH! HA HA HA HA!

98
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,000
ONE RIDE...

99
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:27,875
THEN WE'RE OFF TO
THE NORTH POLE...

100
00:05:27,917 --> 00:05:29,291
AIRBENDER'S HONOR.

101
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,834
THIS SOUNDED LIKE
FUN AT FIRST,

102
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,208
BUT NOW THAT
I'M HERE,

103
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:36,041
I'M STARTING TO HAVE
SECOND THOUGHTS!

104
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,959
[LAUGHING]

105
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,458
[SCREAMING]

106
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,250
Aang: YEAH!

107
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:44,166
HA HA HA HA!

108
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,792
[SCREAMING]

109
00:05:57,792 --> 00:05:58,500
[SCREAMS]

110
00:05:58,542 --> 00:05:59,625
I'M ON IT!

111
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:04,917
[SCREAMING]

112
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:08,125
MEN, YOU'LL BE GOING
OFF TO COMBAT SOON.

113
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:10,208
IT'S IMPORTANT THAT YOU
BE PREPARED FOR ANYTHING.

114
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:21,542
AANG, DO SOMETHING!

115
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,166
USE YOUR AIRBENDING!

116
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:25,125
YEAH! GOOD IDEA!

117
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:26,583
THAT WILL MAKE US
GO EVEN FASTER.

118
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,083
[SCREAMING]

119
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:42,834
[SIGHS]

120
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:46,667
[SCREAMING]

121
00:07:02,792 --> 00:07:03,417
Aang: SORRY!

122
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,125
[ALL SCREAM]

123
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:17,291
[HUMMING]

124
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,667
MY CABBAGES!

125
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:23,834
YOU'RE GONNA
PAY FOR THIS!

126
00:07:25,792 --> 00:07:27,208
TWO CABBAGES, PLEASE.

127
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:42,083
HMM?

128
00:07:42,125 --> 00:07:43,709
YOUR MAJESTY,

129
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:44,792
THESE JUVENILES
WERE ARRESTED

130
00:07:44,834 --> 00:07:46,250
FOR VANDALISM,

131
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:48,041
TRAVELING UNDER
FALSE PRETENSES,

132
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,458
AND MALICIOUS
DESTRUCTION
OF CABBAGES.

133
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,041
OFF WITH
THEIR HEADS!

134
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:52,250
ONE FOR EACH
HEAD OF CABBAGE!

135
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:53,792
SILENCE!

136
00:07:53,834 --> 00:07:55,750
ONLY THE KING CAN
PASS DOWN JUDGMENT.

137
00:07:55,792 --> 00:07:57,291
WHAT IS YOUR
JUDGMENT, SIRE?

138
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:58,959
HMM.

139
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:04,250
[STAMMERING]

140
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:09,917
[WHISTLING]

141
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:12,083
THROW THEM...

142
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,291
A FEAST.

143
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,125
UGH!

144
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,083
HUH?

145
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:25,208
[CHUCKLES]

146
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:27,000
THE PEOPLE IN MY CITY

147
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:29,834
HAVE GOTTEN FAT
FROM TOO MANY FEASTS.

148
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:33,041
SO, I HOPE YOU LIKE YOUR
CHICKEN WITH NO SKIN.

149
00:08:33,083 --> 00:08:34,834
THANKS, BUT I DON'T
EAT MEAT.

150
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:36,166
HOW ABOUT YOU?

151
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,375
I BET YOU LIKE MEAT.

152
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:40,917
[GRUNTS]

153
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:42,500
IS IT JUST ME,

154
00:08:42,542 --> 00:08:45,208
OR IS THIS GUY'S CROWN
A LITTLE CROOKED?

155
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:48,417
SO, TELL ME,
YOUNG BALD ONE,

156
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:49,750
WHERE ARE
YOU FROM?

157
00:08:49,792 --> 00:08:53,166
I'M FROM KANGAROO ISLAND.

158
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:55,834
OH, KANGAROO ISLAND, EH?

159
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:59,583
I HEAR THAT PLACE
IS REALLY HOPPING.

160
00:08:59,625 --> 00:09:01,625
[MAN COUGHS]

161
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:03,125
[LAUGHS]

162
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,625
WHAT?

163
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:07,709
IT WAS
PRETTY FUNNY.

164
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,083
[YAWNS]

165
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:13,291
ALL THESE GOOD JOKES
ARE MAKING ME TIRED.

166
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:15,792
GUESS IT'S TIME
TO HIT THE HAY.

167
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:20,542
[GASPS]

168
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:23,125
THERE'S AN AIRBENDER
IN OUR PRESENCE,

169
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:25,667
AND NOT JUST
ANY AIRBENDER--

170
00:09:25,709 --> 00:09:27,208
THE AVATAR.

171
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:32,917
NOW, WHAT DO YOU HAVE
TO SAY FOR YOURSELF,

172
00:09:32,959 --> 00:09:34,291
MR. PIPPENPADLOPSICOPOLIS?

173
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:43,333
OK, YOU CAUGHT ME.

174
00:09:43,375 --> 00:09:45,208
I'M THE AVATAR...

175
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,500
DOING MY AVATAR THING,

176
00:09:46,542 --> 00:09:48,458
KEEPING THE WORLD SAFE.

177
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,000
EVERYTHING CHECKS OUT.

178
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,291
NO FIREBENDERS HERE.

179
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,875
SO, GOOD WORK, EVERYBODY.

180
00:09:52,917 --> 00:09:54,208
LOVE EACH OTHER,

181
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,625
RESPECT ALL LIFE,

182
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,166
AND DON'T RUN
WITH YOUR SPEARS.

183
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:58,250
WE'LL SEE YOU NEXT TIME!

184
00:10:01,375 --> 00:10:02,792
Katara: YOU CAN'T
KEEP US HERE.

185
00:10:02,834 --> 00:10:05,291
LET US LEAVE!

186
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:06,291
LETTUCE LEAF?

187
00:10:09,834 --> 00:10:11,291
WE'RE IN
SERIOUS TROUBLE.

188
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:13,208
THIS GUY
IS NUTS.

189
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:17,750
TOMORROW, THE AVATAR WILL
FACE 3 DEADLY CHALLENGES.

190
00:10:17,792 --> 00:10:21,375
BUT FOR NOW, THE GUARDS WILL
SHOW YOU TO YOUR CHAMBER.

191
00:10:21,417 --> 00:10:23,125
MY LIEGE,
DO YOU MEAN

192
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:24,291
THE GOOD CHAMBER
OR THE BAD CHAMBER?

193
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:26,041
THE NEWLY-REFURBISHED CHAMBER.

194
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:28,417
WAIT. WHICH ONE ARE
WE TALKING ABOUT?

195
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:31,250
THE ONE THAT USED TO
BE THE BAD CHAMBER...

196
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:34,000
UNTIL THE RECENT
REFURBISHING, THAT IS.

197
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:36,125
OF COURSE, WE'VE BEEN
CALLING IT THE NEW CHAMBER,

198
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:37,709
BUT WE REALLY
SHOULD NUMBER THEM.

199
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:39,208
UH...

200
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,667
TAKE THEM TO
THE REFURBISHED CHAMBER

201
00:10:40,709 --> 00:10:42,166
THAT WAS ONCE BAD.

202
00:10:50,709 --> 00:10:52,792
Katara: THIS IS
A PRISON CELL?

203
00:10:52,834 --> 00:10:54,166
BUT IT'S SO NICE.

204
00:10:54,208 --> 00:10:56,291
HE DID SAY IT WAS
NEWLY REFURBISHED.

205
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:58,625
NICE OR NOT,
WE'RE PRISONERS.

206
00:10:58,667 --> 00:11:00,917
I WONDER WHAT THESE
CHALLENGES ARE GONNA BE.

207
00:11:00,959 --> 00:11:03,166
WE'RE NOT STICKING
AROUND TO FIND OUT.

208
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:05,125
THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOME WAY OUT OF HERE.

209
00:11:05,166 --> 00:11:06,000
THE AIR VENTS!

210
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,083
IF YOU THINK
WE'RE GONNA FIT
THROUGH THERE,

211
00:11:10,125 --> 00:11:11,750
YOU'RE CRAZIER
THAN THAT KING.

212
00:11:11,792 --> 00:11:13,166
WE CAN'T.

213
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,417
BUT MOMO CAN.

214
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:19,041
MOMO, I NEED
YOU TO FIND APPA

215
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:20,333
AND BUST US
OUT OF HERE.

216
00:11:20,375 --> 00:11:22,041
[GROANS]

217
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:29,375
GO ON, BOY!

218
00:11:29,417 --> 00:11:31,750
GET APPA!

219
00:11:31,792 --> 00:11:34,375
EH, HOW WAS APPA SUPPOSED
TO SAVE US ANYWAY?

220
00:11:34,417 --> 00:11:37,208
APPA IS A 10-TON
FLYING BISON.

221
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:39,500
I THINK HE COULD FIGURE
SOMETHING OUT.

222
00:11:39,542 --> 00:11:42,458
WELL, NO POINT
ARGUING ABOUT IT NOW.

223
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,333
GET SOME REST, AANG.

224
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:45,917
LOOKS LIKE YOU'LL
NEED IT FOR TOMORROW.

225
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:50,250
[SNORING]

226
00:11:54,709 --> 00:11:57,166
SOKKA? KATARA?!

227
00:11:57,208 --> 00:11:59,125
WHERE ARE MY FRIENDS?!

228
00:11:59,166 --> 00:12:01,208
THE KING WILL FREE THEM
IF YOU COMPLETE
YOUR CHALLENGES.

229
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:03,208
AND IF I FAIL?

230
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:04,333
HE DIDN'T SAY.

231
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:05,834
YOUR STAFF, PLEASE?

232
00:12:11,834 --> 00:12:14,083
FIRST, AVATAR,

233
00:12:14,125 --> 00:12:16,166
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF MY NEW OUTFIT?

234
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:17,417
I WANT YOUR HONEST OPINION.

235
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,542
[MAN COUGHS]

236
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,542
I'M WAITING.

237
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:23,709
I...

238
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,166
GUESS IT'S FINE.

239
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:26,542
EXCELLENT.

240
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,250
YOU'VE PASSED
THE FIRST TEST.

241
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:28,917
REALLY?

242
00:12:28,959 --> 00:12:30,500
WELL...

243
00:12:30,542 --> 00:12:32,000
NOT ONE OF
THE DEADLY TESTS.

244
00:12:32,041 --> 00:12:34,208
THE REAL CHALLENGES
ARE MUCH MORE...

245
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:34,875
CHALLENGING.

246
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:40,333
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR YOUR CRAZY GAMES.

247
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:42,625
GIVE ME MY FRIENDS BACK.
WE'RE LEAVING!

248
00:12:42,667 --> 00:12:45,792
OH, I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT REFUSE,

249
